 <table-wrap-foot>
  <fn fn-type="other" id="ngtab1.1">
   <label>a</label>
   <p>Refer to the pandemic and epidemic definitions in the text and cited references, particularly references 
    <xref rid="B7" ref-type="bibr">7</xref> and 
    <xref rid="B8" ref-type="bibr">8</xref>. The table is not comprehensive but lists notable emergences of historical importance. Many of these diseases have emerged/reemerged on multiple occasions. For most historical pandemics, estimated numbers of deaths have varied widely, and figures cannot be considered accurate.
   </p>
  </fn>
  <fn fn-type="other" id="ngtab1.2">
   <label>b</label>
   <p>Zika deaths occur mostly 
    <italic>in utero</italic> or in newborns; death in older children and adults is rare.
   </p>
  </fn>
 </table-wrap-foot>
</table-wrap>
